p <- ggplot(gapminder, mapping = aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp))
p + geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", color = "red") +
  scale_x_log10(label = scales::label_dollar()) +
  labs(x = "GDP per capita", y = "Years",
       title = "Life Expectancy and GDP",
       caption = "Source: Gapminder") +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Gapminder boxplot (slide 30)

gapminder |> filter(year == 2007) |>
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = continent, y = lifeExp, fill = continent)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  guides(fill = "none")

A polished plot (slide 38)

gapminder
## # A tibble: 1,704 × 6
##    country     continent  year lifeExp      pop gdpPercap

##  7 Afghanistan Asia       1982    39.9 12881816      978.

## # … with 1,694 more rows
p <- ggplot(gapminder, mapping = aes(x = gdpPercap, y = lifeExp))
p + geom_point(alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  scale_x_log10(label = scales::label_dollar()) +
  labs(x = "GDP per capita", y = "Life Expectancy in Years",
       title = "Economic Growth and Life Expectancy",
       subtitle = "Data points are country-years",
       caption = "Source: Gapminder") +
  theme_bw()
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
